{{Infobox lake | name = Morské oko | image = Národná prírodná rezervácia Morské oko - jazero, CHKO Vihorlat (03).jpg | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Vihorlat Mountains]] | coords = {{coord|48|54|56|N|22|11|54|E|type:waterbody_region:SK|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = | outflow = | catchment = | basin_countries = Slovakia | length = | width = | area = {{convert|13|ha|abbr=on}} | depth = | max-depth = {{convert|25.1|m|abbr=on}} | volume = | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = {{convert|618|m|abbr=on}} | frozen = | islands = | cities = }} '''Morské oko''' (called ''Veľké Vihorlatské jazero'' in the past; literally Sea Eye) is a lake in the [[Vihorlat Mountains]] in east [[Slovakia]]. It is at 618&nbsp;[[metre|m]], covers 0.13&nbsp;km² with a maximum depth of 25.1&nbsp;m. It is a national nature reserve (covering 1.08&nbsp;km²) since 1984 and part of the [[Vihorlat Protected Landscape Area]]. Among the many fish are trout.
